addOrderFiller(address).details: Whitelist an order filler. Only the owner of this contract can call this  function.

params._filler: : Address that will call 'fillOrder()' within this contract

addVault(address).details: Add a vault for trading. Vault must inherit 'VaultBase.sol' and meet the vault standard for proper functionality. Only the owner of this contract can call  this function.

changeTokenMinimumDeposit(uint256,addres.details: Change the minimum deposit amount for an ERC20 token when creating a trade. ERC20 token must already be mapped to a holding strategy before calling this function. Only the owner of this contract can call this function.

params._resolver: : Gelato resolver contract used to find the router and swap path that provides the highest output amount.
params._routers: : Approved routers used for executing swaps. No new routers can be added after deploying this contract.
params._slippagePoints: : Highest acceptable slippage amount when executing swaps

createTrade(uint256,address[],uint256[],.notice: Create a trade with one of the approved vaults. The format for '_tokens', '_amounts', and '_times' is specific to the vault. Refer to the vault being used to verify the correct data format. Trades are only created with active vaults. The strating amount of the trade is deposited upon creating a trade. A deposit fee is taken from the deposited amount. When Gelato is active, a task is created for each open order.

params._amounts: : Specific to the vault used. Refer to vault documentation.
params._maxGas: : In gwei. The maximum gas price that any order within this trade can be executed at.
params._times: : Specific to the vault used. Refer to vault documentation.
params._tokens: : Specific to the vault used. Refer to vault documentation.

deactivateOrderFiller(address).details: Revokes order filling permissions from an address. Only the owner of this  contract can call this function.

params._filler: : Address that will have its order filling permissions revoked

deactivateRouter(address).details: Deactivated router will no longer be able to be used for filling orders. A deactivated router cannot be reactivated. Only the owner of this contract can  call this function.

deactivateToken(uint256,address).details: Deactivate an ERC20 token for a vault. Once a token is deactivated, it cannot be reactivated. Only the owner can call this function.

deactivateVault(address).details: Disables the 'createTrade', 'fillOrder', and 'fillOrderGelato' functions. Once a vault is deactivated, users will only be able to withdraw their trades. Deactivated vaults cannot be reactivated. Only the owner of this contract can  call this function.

depositGas(address).notice: Deposit ETH to pay for gas cost accrued from filling orders. ETH deposited is automatically taken from the order owners balance when their orders are filled. User is able to withdraw their balance of ETH at any point in time. This function is not callable when 'isPaused()' == true.

params._receiver: : Address that is credited with the deposited ETH

fillOrder(uint256,uint256,address,addres.notice: Fill open orders when trade conditions are met. Only approved order fillers can call this function. This function will only be used if the use of Gelato is stopped. Call 'findBestPath()' in Resolver.sol first to get the router and path with the highest output amount. Caller is refunded the gas cost from the ETH the order owner has deposited.

params._path: : Swap path used to fill the order
params._router: : Router used to fill the order

fillOrderGelato(uint256,uint256,address,.notice: Fill open orders when trade conditions are met. Only Gelato executors can call this function. This function is the primary method used to fill orders.  If Gelato is no longer used, orders are filled through calling 'fillOrder()' instead. Gelato executor will call 'checker()' in Resolver.sol first to get the  router and path with the highest output amount. Gelato executor is refunded the  gas cost from the ETH the order owner has deposited.

params._path: : Swap path used to fill the order
params._router: : Router used to fill the order

gelatoSettings(address,address,bool).details: Configure Gelato settings. Enable/disable filling orders with Gelato. Only  the owner of this contract can call this function.

params._gelato: : true: Gelato fills orders; false: Dev fills orders
params._pokeMe: : Gelato contract that will call this contract
params._resolver: : Contract that the Gelato executor will call for the input data used when calling this contract.

returns._0: Number of open orders in the vault
Number of orders created in the vault

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pause().details: After calling, 'createTrade', 'fillOrder', 'fillOrderGelato', and 'depositGas' functions will be disabled. Users will only be able to withdraw their trades and any deposited gas. Only the owner of this contract can call this function.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

priceMultiplier(uint256).notice: The prices used when creating trades need to be multiplied by the value returned from this function. This is done to handle the decimals.

returns._0: Value to multiply with the price

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setOrderFillers(bool).details: Restrict order filling to a whitelist of addresses or allow any address to fill orders. Only the owner of this contract can call this function.

params._whitelist: : true: Only whitelisted addresses can fill orders; false: Any address can fill orders

setSlippage(uint256,uint256).details: Set the slippage amount for each order being filled. Only the owner of this  contract can call this function.

params._slippagePoints: : This value divided by '_slippageBasePoints' gives the  slippage percentage.

setTokenStrategy(uint256,address,address.details: Map a holding strategy contract to an ERC20 token. A token can only be mapped to holding strategy once. Only the owner of this contract can call this function.

params._minDeposit: : Minimum amount of '_token' that can be deposited when creating a trade.

setVaultURI(uint256,string).details: Set the URI of a vault to display an image. Only the owner of this contract  can call this function.

params._vaultId: : Vault that will have its URI set

slippage(uint256).notice: Use to get the minimum amount out of a swap

params._amountIn: : Amount of a given ERC20 token

returns._0: Adjusts '_amountIn' to account for slippage

returns._0: ERC20 token address
Number of ERC20 tokens mapped to a holding strategy in a vault

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unpause().details: Enables 'createTrade', 'fillOrder', 'fillOrderGelato', and 'depositGas' functions. Only the owner of this contract can call this function.

returns._0: 0: Not added to this contract; 1 = Active vault; 2 = Deactivated vault

params._end: : End index of 'openOrderIds' within the vault
params._start: : Start index of 'openOrderIds' within the vault

returns._0: Open orders inside the given range

returns._0: Order details
